This paper discusses the combination of the Information Bottleneck model with deep learning, which is a topic that falls under the subfield of machine learning. Specifically, the paper focuses on the Deep Variational Information Bottleneck and its assumptions, which are related to optimization and information theory. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
